	<div id="date">Monday, April 9, 2012</div>	
<div class="post">
	<h1 class="posttitle"><a href="http://theredspoonblog.com/2012/04/09/whole-wheat-pita-bread/" title="Permanent Link to whole wheat pita bread">whole wheat pita bread</a></h1>
	


	<div class="article"><p><a title="whole wheat pita bread" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/theredspoonblog/7052482779/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackPageview','/yoast-ga/outbound-article/http://www.flickr.com']);"><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7128/7052482779_1db0bb14d7.jpg" alt="whole wheat pita bread" width="500" height="334" /></a></p>
<p>I have had the worst case of cooking block these past two weeks. Surprisingly the market started to get new, shiny, colorful spring things, like <em>purple</em> potatoes and bright green peas, and despite bringing them home and trying to decide which of my 42 potato recipes was going to feature some purple flair or which pea crostini version I wanted to audition, I barely cooked them in time and did so only halfheartedly. It only spiraled down from there &#8212; even the ice cream, ahem, two ice cream flavors we ate were ehh; tolerable to top off an Easter luncheon at best, but only because it was cold and involved a sugary custard gone <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/theredspoonblog/7052479951/in/photostream" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackPageview','/yoast-ga/outbound-article/http://www.flickr.com']);">wildly lemon</a>. Then there was the <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/theredspoonblog/6914895774/in/photostream" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackPageview','/yoast-ga/outbound-article/http://www.flickr.com']);">little boss</a> who had decided to take on a runny nose and lost; lost severely as there were many a fight to clear breathing holes and gently wipe, or ya know, attempt a gentle wipe when really it was an head-lock battle of mom vs. tiny screaming human with a soft pillow to wipe off cruddies and a torturous (problem solving, mind you) suctioning device that ended up as more of an empty threat since <em>there was going to be none of that</em>.</p>
<p><a title="dumping" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/theredspoonblog/7052480237/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackPageview','/yoast-ga/outbound-article/http://www.flickr.com']);"><img src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5200/7052480237_6cb98fdf62.jpg" alt="dumping" width="500" height="334" /></a></p>
<p><a title="grinding" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/theredspoonblog/7052480475/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackPageview','/yoast-ga/outbound-article/http://www.flickr.com']);"><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7131/7052480475_55a9aaa4b9.jpg" alt="grinding" width="500" height="334" /></a></p>
<p><a title="ground" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/theredspoonblog/7052480797/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackPageview','/yoast-ga/outbound-article/http://www.flickr.com']);"><img src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5319/7052480797_0d21d696cb.jpg" alt="ground" width="500" height="334" /></a></p>
<p>And alas, after week one of cooking absolutely nothing, at least nothing worth even mentioning, because, hey, I can&#8217;t even remember if I did, I got caught up in the edge-of-my-seat finale of <a href="http://www.foodnetwork.com/worst-cooks-in-america/index.html" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackPageview','/yoast-ga/outbound-article/http://www.foodnetwork.com']);">Worst Cooks in America</a>. I don&#8217;t even like reality shows, but Anne &#8212; whom I call my sister, except we&#8217;ve never met and only one of us knows the other exists; yeah my husband rolls his eyes too &#8212; is the supastar and as you can tell my chef crush is <em>raging huge</em> and <em>I will watch anything she is in</em>. No joke. I watched Next Iron Chef: Super Chef until she was wrongfully voted off. Then out of policy (with a side of spite) I avoided that show like the plague. But anyways, I got caught up in the last nail biting episode, hoping to get like a manicure out of the ordeal at the very least, when at last I was able to do my flail about the house in glee dance that looks something like a mesh of <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jRwsTyUPIYE" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackPageview','/yoast-ga/outbound-article/http://www.youtube.com']);">Snoopy</a> and <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5xi4O1yi6b0" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackPageview','/yoast-ga/outbound-article/http://www.youtube.com']);">Elaine</a> (basically, she won).</p>
<p><a title="spicy flour" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/theredspoonblog/6906391162/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackPageview','/yoast-ga/outbound-article/http://www.flickr.com']);"><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7084/6906391162_0828f12aa8.jpg" alt="spicy flour" width="500" height="334" /></a></p>
<p><a title="yeast: activated" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/theredspoonblog/6906391526/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackPageview','/yoast-ga/outbound-article/http://www.flickr.com']);"><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7251/6906391526_c649dda7a8.jpg" alt="yeast: activated" width="500" height="334" /></a></p>
<p><a title="whole wheat dough" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/theredspoonblog/7052481481/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackPageview','/yoast-ga/outbound-article/http://www.flickr.com']);"><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7273/7052481481_3ef15e260f.jpg" alt="whole wheat dough" width="500" height="334" /></a></p>
<p> <a href="http://theredspoonblog.com/2012/04/09/whole-wheat-pita-bread/#more-6172"  class="more-link">Continue spooning &raquo;</a></p>
</div>
